description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Hayate no Gotoku!.

Since the tender age of nine, Hayate Ayasaki has busted his behind at various part-time jobs to support his degenerate gambler parents. And how do they repay their son's selfless generosity? By selling his organs to the yakuza to cover their debts! But fate throws Hayate a bone...sort of. Now the butler of a wealthy young lady, Hayate can finally pay back his debts, and it'll only take him 40 years to do it.
name: Hayate the Combat Butler

description:
With a special preview/launchat the Birmingham International Comics Show (BICS) on 03 & 04 October 2009, and officially launched a few days later on 06 october 2009, Buskers has received critical acclaim within a month of publication. Even before it was launched, plans had begun for a major movie adaptation.Since the story revolves around the lives ofstreet musicians,a limited edition came available with a CD with musicperformed by The Bullits.

The story revolves around a big City banker who attempted to commit suicide after his lost his job. With life as he knew it at an end, but unable to end it all, he was forced to re-evaluate his life. It isn't long before he is entagled among the lives of Londonstreet performers; the eponymous Buskers.
name: Buskers

description:
Regardless of Jonah's hatred of weapons and violence, his occupation requires him to exercise both extremely well in the service of well-known arms dealer Koko Hekmatyar and her crew of mercenaries. Their journey through the underbelly of the world's arms markets may lead to damnation, but hopefully someday Jonah will make his way back to the light. One thing is for certain: the trip back from hell will be long and difficult.

description:
Published before the format that would become comics had been formalized this was not comic per-say, but magazine sized, this however was still one of the first publications to have original comics in it, and not be made up of just the reprints of newspaper strips.

It is also the place where the first work of Will Eisner and Bob Kane was seen.
name: Wow, What A Magazine!
